    gx_max_pain:'Max Pain',
    gx_disclaimer:'Delayed data. GEX levels are estimates based on mathematical models and do not constitute investment advice. Trading involves risk of loss.',
    gx_edu_title:'What is Gamma Exposure (GEX)?',
    gx_edu_what_title:'What is GEX?',
    gx_edu_what:'Gamma Exposure (GEX) measures the <strong>options volume</strong> that market makers (large banks and institutions) need to hedge at each price level. When a market maker sells an option, they must buy or sell the underlying asset to protect themselves. GEX shows <strong>WHERE</strong> and <strong>HOW MUCH</strong> they need to do this.',
    gx_edu_zero_title:'Zero Gamma (Gamma Flip)',
    gx_edu_zero:'The <strong>Zero Gamma</strong> level is where total exposure flips from positive to negative. <strong>Above zero gamma</strong>, market makers buy dips and sell rallies (suppress volatility). <strong>Below zero gamma</strong>, they do the opposite and AMPLIFY movements. It\'s the most important level of the day.',
    gx_edu_walls_title:'Put Wall & Call Wall',
    gx_edu_walls:'The <strong>Put Wall</strong> is the strike with the largest put options concentration — it acts as <strong>strong support</strong> because market makers buy the asset at this level. The <strong>Call Wall</strong> is the opposite — largest call concentration, acts as <strong>resistance</strong> because they sell there.',
    gx_edu_hvl_title:'HVL (High Volume Level)',
    gx_edu_hvl:'The <strong>HVL</strong> is the strike with the highest absolute gamma volume. Price tends to "stick" to this level during the day because market makers are constantly hedging there. If price breaks through HVL with force, it usually signals a <strong>strong directional move</strong>.',
    gx_edu_posneg_title:'Positive vs Negative GEX',
    gx_edu_posneg:'<strong>Positive GEX</strong> (total &gt; 0): Market is "pinned" — market makers absorb moves. Tight range days. <strong>Negative GEX</strong> (total &lt; 0): Market is "loose" — moves are amplified. High volatility days. This is when stops get swept and trends accelerate.',
    gx_edu_use_title:'How to use in trading?',
    gx_edu_use:'Use <strong>Zero Gamma</strong> as the key level of the day. If price is above it, trade mean reversions. If below, trade breakouts and trends. The <strong>Put Wall</strong> is reliable support and the <strong>Call Wall</strong> is resistance. Combine with your technical analysis to increase accuracy.',
